Product description

CPU:Intel Core i7  |  Style:PC

Acer Spin 5 SP513-52N-85LZ Touch PC comes with these high level specs: 8th Generation Intel Core i7-8550U Processor 1.8GHz with Turbo Boost Technology up to 4.0GHz (8MB Smart cache), Windows 10 Home, 13.3" Full HD (1920 x 1080) widescreen LED-backlit IPS display - Multi-touch screen, supporting 10-finger touch, Intel UHD Graphics 620, 8GB DDR4 Dual Channel Memory, 256GB SSD, Secure Digital (SD) card reader, Acer True Harmony Technology, Two Built-in Stereo Speakers, 802.11ac Wi-Fi featuring 2x2 MU-MIMO technology (Dual-Band 2.4GHz and 5GHz), Bluetooth 4.1, HD Webcam (1280 x 720) supporting High Dynamic Range (HDR), 1 - USB 3.1 Type C Gen 1 port (up to 5 Gbps), DisplayPort over USB-C, 2 - USB 3.0 Ports (one with Power-off Charging), 1 - USB 2.0 port, 1 - HDMI Port with HDCP support, Acer Fingerprint Reader supporting Windows Hello, 3-cell Li-Ion Battery (4810 mAh), Up to 13-hours Battery Life, 3.31 lbs. | 1.5 kg (system unit only, Alexa Built-in (NX.GR7AA.013).

CPU: Intel Core i7Style: PCVerified Purchase
Originally I gave this a 1 star and posted this angry opinion: It crashes my wifi (tp link archer c7) so I cannot use the wifi, the hinge on the monitor pinched my leg painfully through my pants the first time I opened it.

Well, I updated the firmware on my router, so now it works. That is the fix, check their website.

Also, I was originally unimpressed with the tablet feature, but I found myself using it within 24 hours and enjoying it.

Lastly, the OS, Windows 10, is a huge improvement over Windows 8. And for the first time I actually saw the value in Windows tablet mode.

This computer won me over.

Deena Her
4.0 out of 5 starsEverything as expected with a couple downers
April 9, 2019
CPU: Intel Core i7Style: PCVerified Purchase
I watched YouTube videos and did a lot of research before purchasing this item, 2 in 1 Acer Spin 5. I couldn't make up my mind if a 2 in 1 will be for me, but I absolutely love everything about this laptop.

Positives for me:
(1) Backlit keyboard - I absolutely love this feature. It has an Off and On button (located on F8 key) and this was one feature I absolutely wanted. It doesn't have different levels of brightness you can choose from, but I didn't care because I can turn it off and on.

(2) Stylus - I didn't read anywhere that it comes with a stylus, but my order came with one. Absolute plus and it works great.

(3) Charger - Love the size of the charger. It's not bulky at all. Instead, it's this cute little cube that fits into the palm of my hand.

(4) Touchscreen - The touchscreen is amazing and the stylus works well with the screen. Lets just say my toddler wouldn't even let me check it out for myself because she had so much fun with it.

(5) Super thin - This laptop is thin thin thin. It doesn't feel as light as other ones I've seen, but the thinness makes up for it.

(6) SD Card Slot, USB ports, HDMI, thunderbolt, fingerprint, and other features - Amazing! This part was the hardest for me when it came to choosing a new laptop. I didn't want a micro SD slot, I want the regular size one and I wanted to make sure it had enough USB ports, fingerprint and facial recognition features and everything else and this laptop had it all for me.

(7) Key Stroke & Distance - Great! It would be even better if the Page Up and Down buttons weren't next to the arrows button, but I haven't had a problem with it either.

Negatives for me:
(1) The Pad - It seems quite sensitive at times and then at other times, it won't click on what I'm telling it to click on. This was frustrating at times, but I finally got a mouse so I don't think this will bother me as much. It doesn't happen often either. Just once in awhile.

(2) Batter life - It says 13 hours, but after a full charge (without using the laptop while charging), I powered it on and it only said 4 hours with the battery life showing as full and at 100%.

Some features I haven't tried:
(1) Camera - I haven't tried chatting or try using the camera yet so I don't have any opinions about that at this time.
